---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Media guidelines"
  description="How to capture NDA-safe screenshots and recordings of real web apps"
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-10 sm:px-6">
    <a class="text-sm text-slate-300 hover:text-white" href="/portfolio">
      Back to portfolio
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
      Media guidelines
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-slate-300">
      This page is a checklist for recording browser demos and taking screenshots of real client work while minimising NDA and privacy risk.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert mt-10 max-w-none prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-brown-300">
      <h2>What to capture (high signal, low risk)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Navigation and information architecture: sidebar, tabs, breadcrumbs (blur any customer names)
        </li>
        <li>
          List UX: filters, search, sort, pagination, view toggles (blur rows if they contain real data)
        </li>
        <li>
          Empty states and loading states: blank slates, skeletons, spinners
        </li>
        <li>
          Accessibility behaviour: keyboard navigation, visible focus ring, skip-link, aria labels (avoid showing private content)
        </li>
        <li>
          Responsive behaviour: desktop and mobile widths for the same route
        </li>
        <li>
          Modal open/close only (no submit), demonstrating focus trap and escape-to-close
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What to avoid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Customer-identifying data (names, addresses, IDs, account numbers)</li>
        <li>Internal hostnames, API URLs, monitoring domains, auth provider screens</li>
        <li>
          Any create/update/delete submission or anything that could plausibly be a production write
        </li>
        <li>Browser devtools network tab with live headers/tokens</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to redact safely</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Prefer blurred table bodies over pixelating individual fields</li>
        <li>Mask the browser address bar if URLs are sensitive</li>
        <li>Use a consistent blur style so the visuals still look professional</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Suggested “3 minute project” recording structure</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Context: what the page is for (10–15 seconds)</li>
        <li>User journey: one read-only workflow (60–90 seconds)</li>
        <li>Quality: show responsiveness and keyboard navigation (30–45 seconds)</li>
        <li>Outcome: the result for users/business (10–15 seconds)</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
